Title: Width
JsName: width
DataAttribute: data-width
Category: Core
Description: The initial size of the canvas during loading or the width for particular layouts (e.g. page layout).
ShowInSideBar: false
Since: 0.9.4
---

<h2>Description</h2>
<p>
    By default alphaTab is responsive and resizes itself automatically to the available width of the parent element. This setting allows fixing alphaTab to a given width without dynamic resizing.
    Of course this can also be achieved by fixing the parent element width. 
</p>

<h2>Types</h2>

<table class="table table-striped table-condensed type-table">
    <thead>
        <tr>
            <th>Type</th>
            <th>Values</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>    
    <tbody>    
        <tr>
            <td><code>int <span class="code-badge">all</span></td>
            <td>
                <code>500</code><br />
                <code>1024</code>
            </td>
        </tr>   
    </tbody>
</table>

<h2>Default Value</h2>

<code>-1<code> (auto sizing)

<h2>Example - C#</h2>

<pre>
<code class="language-csharp line-numbers">
var settings = Settings.Defaults;
settings.Width = 500;
</code>
</pre>


<h2>Example - JavaScript</h2>

<pre>
<code class="language-javascript line-numbers">
var settings = {
    width: 500
};
var api = new alphaTab.platform.javaScript.AlphaTabApi(document.querySelector('#alphaTab'), settings);
var japi = $('#alphaTab').alphaTab(settings);
</code>
</pre>

<h2>Example - HTML</h2>

<pre>
<code class="language-html line-numbers">
&lt;div id="alphaTab" data-width="500"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
</code>
</pre>
